    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - BE 200, CE 200, CE 300 Model - CHASSIS FEATURES - ESC - SOLENOID
        POWER CIRCUIT
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="x08290184">
        <title>ESC - SOLENOID POWER CIRCUIT</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Circuit Functions</title>
            <figure id="f082901025" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G082901025.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="432px"/>
                <caption>Solenoid Power Function Diagram</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SOLENOID POWER CIRCUIT (TO REMOTE AIR SOLENOID MODULE)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. ELECTRICAL SYSTEM CONTROLLER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. KEY SWITCH</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The solenoid power circuit provides battery voltage to the remote air solenoid modules. This voltage
                is provided on one side of the module solenoids. During normal operation the ESC will enable this
                voltage when the key is in the accessory or ignition position. Certain solenoid fault conditions will
                cause the ESC to disable the voltage.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
